  "title": "Test Engineer (Contract, Semiconductor)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Develop and implement ATE test programs for Digital, Power Management, RF &amp; Mixed Signal ICs in wafer sort and packaged stages.</li>\n  <li>Design and debug test hardware including load boards and probe cards, supporting first silicon debug and production release.</li>\n  <li>Perform device characterization across PVT, optimizing digital test patterns, yield, and test time.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams in hardware, product engineering, design, quality, and foundry to enhance test methodologies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Electronics or Electrical Engineering from a reputed university.</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of hands-on experience in a <strong>lab environment, including setup, testing, and troubleshooting of electronic circuits</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in digital and analog electronics, with experience in Python scripting for automation.</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to work independently and optimize test processes.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in <strong>MS Word</strong> to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R21100996</p>",
